HEADWORD: Discontinuor
<hw>Dis`con*tin"u*or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>One who deprives another of the possession of an estate by
discontinuance. See <er>Discontinuance</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discontinuous</ent>⟦br⟧
